HEADWORD: Muset
<hw>Mu"set</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OF.
<ets>mussette</ets>, dim. of <ets>musse</ets>, <ets>muce</ets>, a hiding
place, fr. F. <ets>musser</ets>, OF. <ets>mucier</ets>,
<ets>muchier</ets>, to conceal, hide. Cf. <er>Micher</er>.]</ety> <def>A
small hole or gap through which a wild animal passes; a muse.</def>
